Newly crowned Miss Universe 2019 South Africa's Zozibini Tunzi poses during a press conference after the 2019 Miss Universe pageant at the Tyler Perry Studios in Atlanta, Georgia on December 8, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Newly crowned Miss Universe 2019 Zozibini Tunzi has thanked South Africans for their support after she was crowned on Sunday. The Eastern Cape beauty took the title at the pageant in Atlanta in the US. "I don't think I have ever had as much support as I did coming into the Miss South Africa crown and so I think this will be something extra special for everyone back at home. READ: Zozibini Tunzi crowned 2019 Miss Universe I just want to tell them that I love them so much and thank you for all the support they have shown me for the past four months", said Tunzi. Tunzi won the pageant against Puerto Rico's Madison Anderson and Mexico's Sofía Aragon. The 26-year-old takes over from Catriona Gray of the Philippines. Several people including Trevor Noah, Oprah Winfrey, and President Cyril Ramaphosa have taken to social media to congratulate Zozibini.